ncheff, Courtney,', 'narrator.', 'Read by Courtney Encheff.', "Catch up with the original Curvy Girl Club as adults in this full-length story told from alternating points of view!Life has a way of pulling friends in different directions. Not all of them are good. Five friends found each other senior year of high school, but things have changed since then. From cross-country moves to demanding school and work schedules, keeping a friendship going is harder than any of them anticipated. But when the beloved Waldo's Diner burns down, they have no choice but to put their differences aside and come together to save it. They have mere weeks to raise enough money to buy it back from a greedy corporation and build it to what it once was. What started out as a mission to save Waldo's Diner turns into a lesson instead: you can't always go back to the way things were. Some things are meant to change. For better or worse. Start reading The Curvy Girl Club: All Grown Up to see where the characters you love are as adults. You'll love this heartwarming, raw story of friendship, growth, and redemption.", 'The curvy girl club', 'All grown up', 'The Curvy Girl Club', '11.5', 'All grown up', 'Kelsie Stelting', 'Kelsie Stelting Creative, LLC', 'The Curvy Girl Club', '11.5'], 'author_raw': 'Stelting, Kelsie, author.', 'author_alt': 'Kelsie Stelting.', 'author': 'Kelsie Stelting', 'ss_title_autocomplete': 'All grown up', 'ss_author_autocomplete': 'Kelsie Stelting', 'series': ['The curvy girl club'], 'ss_od_series': 'The Curvy Girl Club', 'fs_od_reading_order': 11.5, 'additional_contributor': ['Encheff, Courtney,', 'narrator.'], 'opac_label': 'ONLINE', 'suppressed': False, 'deleted': False, 'created_date': '2023-09-12T17:07:54Z', 'publishYear': 2023, 'material_type': 'eAudiobook', 'ss_type': 'catalog', 'ss_grouping': 'all-grown-up-kelsie-stelting-english', 'call_number': 'eAUDIO', 'ss_lc_call_number': 'PZ7.1.S74', 'fs_call_number': 0, 'isbn': ['9798368990804', '979-8368990804'], 'subjects